<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangsu City `Hot Place' for Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2603140694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1324 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2603140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, March 26 (XINHUA) -- The development zone 
in Yangzhou city, Jiangsu Province, has become a hot place for 
overseas investment. 
  Business people from the United States, France, Brazil, Hong 
Kong and Taiwan are streaming into the city to set up 
enterprises and develop land. 
  According to Qian Yurong, chairman of the Yangzhou Economic 
and Technological Development Zone, the zone has accommodated 56 
foreign-funded enterprises over the past year since its founding. 
  These enterprises are involved in the fields of metallurgy, 
light and textile industries, machinery, commerce and trade and 
infrastructure facilities. 
  Ten of them already have gone into production. 
  Located in the Chang Jiang River valley, the development 
zone 
is developing 9.8 square kilometers of areas in the first 
construction phase. 
  So far infrastructure construction on one half of the area 
has been completed. 
  Enterprises in the zone generated output value totalling 310 
million yuan and 70 million yuan in profits and taxes last year. 

</TEXT>

