<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Nuclear Generator Begins Trial Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2503154894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1407 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2503154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 25 (XINHUA) -- The No. 2 Generating 
Unit at the Daya Bay Nuclear Power Plant began full capacity 
trial operation from 19:15 [1115 GMT] Beijing time today. 
  Trial operations at 15, 30, 50, 75, 87 and 97 percent of its 
designed capacity of 900,000 kilowatts have been conducted since 
February 7, according to the Shenzhen-based Guangdong Nuclear 
Power Joint Venture Company. 
  The trial operation, conducted under the supervision of the 
State Nuclear Safety Bureau, has been a success, meeting all 
technical and safety norms in all stages, it was announced. 
  The No. 2 Generating Unit will start commercial operation 
after every planned test proves a success during a period of 
trial operation at full capacity. 
  The No. 1 Generating Unit started commercial production on 
February 1 this year. 
  The Daya Bay Nuclear Power Plant, with two generating units, 
is about 45 kilometers from the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone 
and 55 kilometers from Hong Kong. 

</TEXT>

