<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Archives Conference Committee Meeting Held in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2603141194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1345 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2603141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 26 (XINHUA) -- The organizing 
committee of the Thirteenth International Archives Conference 
(IAC) called its second meeting Thursday [24 March] in Beijing. 
  Luo Gan, state councilor and secretary-general of the State 
Council spoke at the meeting. 
  Wang Gang, director of the State Archives Bureau and vice- 
chairman of the organizing committee, gave a report on the 
preparatory work for the coming conference, which is scheduled 
to be held in Beijing in 1996. 
  Luo, chairman of the organizing committee, stressed the 
importance of good preparatory work for the IAC conference, 
saying that the membership will be expanded to the municipal 
government level to ensure the conference a success. 
  He said that the development of archives work in China has 
gained speed over that of the past decade and a good archives 
system has now taken shape. 
  He said, it is necessary to study and use for reference the 
experience of other countries in archives management and use. 
  The IAC holds an annual meeting every three years, and this 
will be the first to take place in a developing country. 

</TEXT>

