<H3> <TI>   Russia Denies Producing Biological Weapons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803131394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1301 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 28 (XINHUA) -- The Russian Defense 
Ministry today refuted the latest batch of media reports 
alleging that it is continuing a program of creating biological 
weapons, including a new "super-plague" to which the West has no 
antidote. 
  A spokesman for the ministry said that some foreign and 
Russian media have quoted an anonymous intelligence source as 
saying the program was under the Russian Defense Ministry. 
  The spokesman said it is astonishing that the story, 
circulated by Western media in search of sensation, was 
thoughtlessly repeated by some Russian mass media organs. 
  "Russia is neither developing nor producing biological 
weapons," the spokesman stated. 

</TEXT>

