<H3> <TI>   Electronics, Telecommunications Park Founded in Guangdong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803151494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1455 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, March 28 (XINHUA) -- A four sq km 
electronics industrial park was inaugurated today in Guangzhou, 
capital of south China's Guangdong Province. 
  It is aimed to develop advanced electronics and 
telecommunication products and to grow into an international 
electronics and telecommunication research and development 
center. 
  The park is supported by the State Science and Technology 
Commission, the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry 
for National Defense, the Ministry of Electronics Industry and 
the Guangzhou Municipal Committee of Science and Technology. 
  It is intended that program-controlled telephone exchanges 
and digital transmission equipment should soon be produced in 
the new park. Cooperation with world-renowned electronics and 
telecommunications companies is also planned. 

</TEXT>

