<H3> <TI>   Hunan Party Secretary Delivers Report on Changing Concepts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2903105194 Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2903105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The provincial party committee auditorium, which 
has a capacity of 1,000 seats, was packed full on the afternoon 
of the 24 March. Chief responsible persons of various 
organizations directly under the provincial authorities, army 
units, institutes of tertiary education, and scientific research 
institutes gathered here to hear provincial party committee 
Secretary Wang Maolin's report on changing concepts under the 
condition of the socialist market economy. The year 1994 is a 
crucial one in quickening the pace in building the socialist 
market economic structure as well as one in which the greatest 
number of reform measures are to be presented. To help the broad 
cadres have a clear picture of the role of various reform 
measures in building the socialist market economic structure, 
the provincial propaganda department, and work committees of 
organizations directly under the provincial authorities decided 
to sponsor a series of report meetings on deepening reform and 
quickening the pace in building the socialist market economic 
structure. The first report would be made by provincial party 
committee Secretary Wang Maolin. 
  Wang Maolin's report made yesterday had three parts: First, 
to realize renovation of concepts and make a leap in thinking is 
the objective requirement of building the socialist market 
economic structure; second, to outline several major aspects in 
changing concepts and making a leap in thinking; and third, how 
to realize this change in concepts and make a leap in thinking. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

