<F P=102>  OW2803165194 Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1100 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2803165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1100 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National News Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] At the invitation of State President Jiang Zemin, 
ROK President Kim Yong-sam began an official visit to China on 
26 March. This afternoon, President Jiang Zemin presided over a 
ceremony at the Great Hall of the People to warmly welcome 
President Kim Yong-sam and his wife. 
  Present at the welcoming ceremony were Tian Jiyun, vice 
chairman of the National People's Congress Standing Committee; 
Qian Qichen, vice premier of the State Council and minister of 
foreign affairs; Wu Jichuan, chairman of the Chinese Government 
Reception Committee and minister of posts and communications; Li 
Ganliu, vice chairman of the Revolutionary Committee of the 
Chinese Kuomintang; Li Zhongli, minister of finance; Wang 
Zhongyu, minister in charge of the State Economic and Trade 
Commission; Liu Zhongde, minister of culture; and other 
officials. 
  Principal members of President Kim Yong-sam's entourage 
included Minister of Foreign Affairs Han Sung-chu. 
  Born in 1927 on Geoje Island in the ROK's South Kyongsang 
Province, Kim Yong-sam was elected a member of the 14th 
parliament, president of the Democratic Liberal Party [DLP], and 
DLP presidential candidate in 1992. He later became the 14th 
president of the ROK in December 1992. 

</TEXT>

