<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK, PRC Sign Cultural, Double Taxation Agreements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2803131094 Seoul YONHAP in English 1224 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2803131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 28 (YONHAP -- South Korea and China 
concluded a bilateral cultural agreement and a double taxation 
prevention agreement here on Monday during President Kim 
Yong-sam's current official visit to China. 
  The signing took place at the Great Hall of People 
immediately after the summit between President Kim and Chinese 
President Jiang Zemin. 
  The cultural agreement was signed by Foreign Minister Han 
Sung-chu and Chinese Cultural Minister Liu Zhongde and the 
double taxation prevention agreement by Minister Han and Chinese 
Finance Minister Liu Zhongli. 
  Both agreements are to take effect 30 days after the two 
countries notified each other of the completion of their 
respective parliamentary ratification and other necessary 
domestic procedures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

