<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Dissidents Said To Send Democracy Petition to NPC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2903090894 Hong Kong AFP in English 0845 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK2903090894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (AFP)--A group of dissidents in 
Shanghai have sent a petition to parliament, signed by 54 
people, demanding freedom of the press, party pluralism and free 
trade unions, one of the signatories, Bao Ge, said Tuesday. The 
dissident said in a phone conversation from Shanghai that the 
19-point petition had been sent to the National People's 
Congress (NPC) last Friday. 
  Entitled "Blueprint for the political democratisation of the 
state and society in 1994," the petition was signed by 54 people 
"from all walks of life in Shanghai -- intellectuals, academics, 
artists, peasants, workers and private businessmen," Bao said. 
The names includes those of Yang Zhou, Wang Fucheng and Li 
Guotao, prominent Shanghai dissidents, he said. 
  "It is the first signature campaign, and we are going to 
extend the movement nationwide," he said. 

</TEXT>

