<H3> <TI>   Ocean Shipping Group Opens Subsidiary in Xiamen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2903091494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0855 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Xiamen, March 29 (XINHUA) -- China's ocean shipping 
giant, the China Ocean Shipping Group, opened a new subsidiary 
Monday [28 March] in Xiamen, a major port in Fujian Province. 
  Xiamen Ocean Shipping Company, the group's eighth major 
fleet, now owns a French-made luxury passenger liner and two 
large bulk cargo ships. 
  Company officials said the passenger liner will run between 
Hong Kong and Xiamen, while the cargo ships will sail between 
domestic and international ports. 
  China Ocean Shipping Group was newly formed between the 
China 
Ocean Shipping Corporation, China Ocean Shipping Agency, China 
Highway Transport Company and others. 
  The group's fleet of 600 ships now calls at more than 1,000 
ports in over 150 countries around the world. 

