<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   `China National Maize Company' Set Up for Corn Exports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803140494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1351 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 28 (XINHUA) -- A new national company 
specializing in China's maize exports was set up here today. 
  The China National Maize Company, the country's sole agent 
handling maize export business, was jointly established by the 
China National Cereals, Oils and Foodstuffs Import and Export 
Corporation, China Grains Trade Company and nine other companies 
in the cereals and oils trade of the main producing provinces. 
  The company's president, Sun Zhenchi, said that the new 
company, set up in the light of the spirit of the country's new 
reform policy that major commodity items should be managed with 
joint efforts in a unified manner, will give full play to the 
strengths of each partner and play the role of a lever in 
adjusting the domestic supply according to the changes in the 
world market. 
  He said that the setting-up of the new company would bring 
new vitality to the nation's foreign trade development. It will 
join all strands of maize export together to improve the quality 
and standard as well as to increase the competitiveness of 
China's maize in the world market. 
  China's annual maize exports make up about 70 percent of the 
country's total export volume of grains. 

</TEXT>

