<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Calls For Japan To Enter Auto Parts Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2103054894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 21 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2103054894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Moriyasu Okazaki; from NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 21 Mar </F>
Morning Edition] 
  [Text] Beijing, 20 Mar -- At a luncheon meeting with Prime 
Minister Hosokawa on 20 March, Chinese Vice Premier Zhu Rongji 
touched on Japan-China cooperation in the field of automobiles 
and urged Prime Minister Hosokawa to promote the Japanese auto 
industries' access to the Chinese auto parts market, including 
engines. At the same time, Vice Premier Zhu Rongji stressed 
that China will guarantee the quality of Chinese-made rice to be 
imported by Japan. 
  With regard to the auto issue, Vice Premier Zhu said that 
since Japanese companies were reluctant to establish joint 
venture projects in the 1970's, China asked for the cooperation 
of such auto manufacturers as Germany's Volkswagen; that the Big 
Three of the United States have recently started producing auto 
parts in China while Korean companies have indicated their 
intention to produce auto parts; and that Japanese industries 
now can probably afford to cooperate in the area of auto parts 
production. 

</TEXT>

