<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Supports Reform of UN Security Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2103121394 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 21 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2103121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Yuji Kanemoto] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 20 Mar -- During talks with Japanese Prime 
Minister Morihiro Hosokawa on 20 March, Chinese Premier Li Peng 
touched on the reform of the United Nations which Japan has 
proposed. He said: "I support the idea of reforming the UN 
Security Council at an appropriate time." However, he added: 
"Because it will affect interests of various countries, careful 
consideration is necessary." 
  It is said that by these remarks, Li indicated China's 
cautious stand about giving support to Japan for its bid to 
become a permanent member of the UN Security Council through its 
reform. 

</TEXT>

