<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets U.S. `Committee of 100' Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003093794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0852 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin met here today with a delegation from the U.S. 
Committee of 100, headed by the committee's governor and 
well-known architect I.M. Pei. 
  Jiang extended a warm welcome to the delegation on their 
visit to China. 
  The 20-plus delegation members arrived in Beijing Monday [28 
March] at the invitation of the National Committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). 
  The Chinese president said that more exchanges between the 
committee and the CPPCC National Committee will be helpful 
toward promoting understanding between the peoples of China and 
the United States. 
  During the meeting in Zhongnanhai, Pei and other guests 
voiced their suggestions on China's development. 
  The delegation, during their stay in China, will exchange 
views on China's economic development, science and technology, 
education and culture with Chinese scholars and experts as well 
as government officials. 
  Jiang said he hoped the guests would offer valuable 
suggestions on such issues. 

</TEXT>

