<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Jiang Zemin Meets U.S. Publisher </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2903144994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1427 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin had a cordial talk with Reginald K. Brack Jr., 
president of the Time-Warner publishing company of the United 
States, here today. 
  During their meeting, Jiang briefed Brack and his group on 
China's changes since the country took on opening and reform 
programs in the late 1970s. 
  Brack said that his last China tour was made a decade ago. 
This time he was impressed by China's great improvement in 
urban construction, cultural facilities and public health. 
  The Chinese president also introduced to the guests China's 
latest efforts in establishing a socialist market system. 
  Those present at the meeting included Chinese Vice-Foreign 
Minister Liu Huaqiu and J. Stapleton Roy, U.S. Ambassador to 
China. 
  The U.S. visitors are here as guest of the Chinese People's 
Institute for Foreign Affairs. 

</TEXT>

