<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Meets Intel Corporation Chief </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2903134094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1321 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Zou Jiahua met with Craig Barrett, chief operating officer and 
vice-president of the U.S.-based Intel Corporation, and his 
party here this evening. 
  During the meeting, Zou said that China and Intel have 
already had 11 years of cooperation, and that he hoped such 
cooperation will be further developed. 
  Barrett expressed his satisfaction at the cooperation 
between 
his company and the Chinese side, hoping that the two will have 
yet more cooperation in computers and communications. 
  After the meeting, the Chinese vice-premier attended a 
signing ceremony for a technology cooperation agreement between 
Intel and the China Electronics Corporation. 
  The Intel Corporation, founded in 1968, is the biggest 
manufacturer of integrated circuits, and a main maker of 
personal computers, networks and communications. 

</TEXT>

