<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Secretary Reports on Economic Development </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3003123094 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK3003123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While attending the Second Session of the Eighth 
National People's Congress [NPC] in Beijing, Jia Qinglin, Fujian 
Provincial CPC Committee secretary and Fujian governor, said: 
Thanks to the deep-going reform, an export-oriented economic 
structure is gradually taking shape in Fujian. As one of the 
country's pioneers in respect of opening up to the outside 
world, Fujian has built a large number of special economic, 
economic and technological development, coastal open cities and 
open development, Taiwan investment, bonded, high and new 
technological and industrial development, state-level tourism 
and vacation, and urban construction and development zones 
invested and managed by foreign entrepreneurs. Fujian has now 
become one of the most advanced provinces and regions in the 
whole country in terms of reform scale, scope, and policy 
coverage. By the end of last year, Fujian had approved the 
establishment of nearly 13,000 foreign-funded enterprises, 
absorbed more than $5.98 billion of foreign capital, and put 
into operation more than 5,700 enterprises run with three types 
of capital [foreign, Overseas Chinese, and both Chinese and 
foreign capital]. 
  Jia Qinglin stated: Last year, Fujian's domestic gross 
national product registered a 25.4 percent increase over the 
previous year, thereby attaining the goal of quadrupling the 
gross national product one year ahead of schedule. Moreover, 
Fujian's financial revenue topped 100 million yuan for the first 
time. Thanks to the fast growing export-oriented economy, 
Fujian witnessed benign economic growth in 1993. 
  Jia Qinglin noted: This year, despite the introduction of 
new tax and unified exchange rate systems, Fujian's 
export-oriented economy has displayed an incessantly strong 
momentum and vitality. The contracted amount of foreign 
investment and actual amount of foreign investment in the 
province's newly approved enterprises run with three types of 
capital in the January-February period totalled more than $1.33 
billion and $380 million respectively, representing a 11.2 
percent increase and a 49.5 percent increase over the same 
period of last year. Moreover, the province's total export 
volume in the January-February period reached $840 million, 
representing a 44.1 percent increase over the same period of 
last year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-4388 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi061_o_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-061 </AU>
