<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discipline Inspection Plenum Ends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2903132994 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2903132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The third plenary session of the discipline 
inspection commission of the Heilongjiang Provincial CPC 
Committee ended in Harbin today after a three day session. The 
plenary session adopted the resolution and proposed efforts be 
made to conscientiously implement the guidelines of the third 
plenary session of the central discipline inspection commission 
and the plan of the provincial party committee on anticorruption 
struggle, act in line with the overall situation of seizing the 
opportunity, deepening reform, expanding opening up, promoting 
development, and maintaining stability, and unswervingly conduct 
anticorruption struggle. 
  The plenary session discussed and adopted a work report 
given 
by Li Qinglin, member of the standing committee of the 
provincial party committee and secretary of the provincial 
discipline inspection commission, on behalf of the standing 
committee of the provincial discipline inspection commission and 
stressed the necessity of making further efforts to strengthen 
leadership over anticorruption struggle and implement 
responsibility, to expand the degree of work, to further enhance 
the quality of leading cadres in keeping themselves clean and 
self-disciplined and in conducting self- investigation and 
making self-correction, to combine self-investigation and 
self-correction with mass supervision, screening, and evaluation 
of one's honesty, to further strengthen the investigation and 
handling of cases, to resolutely check a number of major and 
appalling cases, to further attend to checking unhealthy trends, 
to stress both temporary solutions and radical measures, to 
expand the degree of work in this aspect, to study supporting 
measures for preventing passive corrupt phenomena in line with 
the implementation of major reform measures, to strengthen mass 
media propaganda on anticorruption struggle, and to persist in 
correct media guidance. 
  The plenary session called on discipline inspection and 
supervision cadres at all levels to conscientiously study, 
strive to enhance their own political and professional level, 
earnestly sum up the work experience of the discipline 
inspection and supervision organs after their amalgamation, give 
better play to the functions of discipline inspection and 
supervision, and make new contributions to promoting the 
province's economic development, reform, and opening up, and 
maintaining social stability. 
  At the end of the session, Li Qinglin explained the relevant 
issues on policy limits for anticorruption work. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-4401 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi061_s_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-061 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Governor Interviewed on Provincial Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1403040394 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1403040394 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During an interview by this station's reporter in 
Beijing yesterday afternoon, Governor Shao Qihui spoke on his 
analysis of the basic principles for Heilongjiang's work. He 
said: For a long time, we have failed to conscientiously handle 
the relationship between reform, development, and stability as 
reiterated in the government work report. We have always 
attached more importance to the total amount of fixed assets and 
shown more interest in developing new projects and increasing 
investment. However, we have not given sufficient attention to 
the available fixed assets and the equipment replacement and 
renovation of old enterprises. As a result, the economy has 
grown rapidly on the one hand, but, on the other, old 
enterprises have experienced difficulties in every step they 
take. Likewise, Heilongjiang has reaped bumper grain harvests 
every year, but peasants' income and local revenue have not 
increased rapidly as grain output has. 
  Governor Shao Qihui analyzed the reasons for such contrast. 
He said: It has resulted both from the problems in our work 
and the oversights and omissions in policies. The basic problem 
lies in our failure in handling well the relationship between 
reform, development, and stability. He continued: To better 
implement major state policies in our specific economic 
activities, we, as the local government, should measure our 
specific work against the government work report and find out 
where we lag behind. We should note both the increase in the 
growth rate of economic development and the increase in the 
number of loss-making large and medium-sized state-owned 
enterprises; and both the substantial improvement in living 
standard with some people becoming well-off ahead of others and 
the great difficulties in the life of some localities and some 
staff members and workers. To successfully address these 
problems, we should refrain from empty sloganeering. 
  Speaking on Heilongjiang's agricultural economy, Governor 
Shao Qihui said: We should not regard the peasant economy as 
the agricultural economy. While attaching importance to the 
interests of peasants, we should also step up efforts to build 
up local and township and village finance; and while speeding up 
the increase in grain output, we should also accelerate the 
development of the nonagricultural economy so that Heilongjiang 
Province will become a large province in agricultural economy at 
an early date instead of a large province in agriculture. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

