<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Punished for Mine Explosion in Heilongjiang </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0803065594 Beijing CHINA DAILY in English 8 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> HK0803065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing CHINA DAILY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [China Daily News: "Officials Punished For Explosion at </F>
Coal Mine"] 
  [Text] Five mine officials have been sacked from their 
posts for their responsibility in a January 24 gas explosion at 
a coal mine in Jixi, Heilongjiang Province. 
  China Labour News reported over the weekend that they will 
face trial. Seven other technicians and officials concerned 
have also been dismissed from their official posts. 
  The explosion killed dozens of coal miners and caused 
damages 
of 4.5 million yuan ($517,000). The main factors in the 
mishap-which caused the northeastern provinces biggest death 
toll from mining since 1949--were poor management and violations 
of the Safety Law in Mines and other rules on safety in mines. 
  Labour officials blamed the frequent accidents in this 
industry on the mishandling or shielding of those at fault. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

