<H3> <TI>   Gansu Governor Addresses Propaganda, Ideological Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2303041594 Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2303041594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In his speech at yesterday's [5 March] provincial 
propaganda and ideological work meeting, Acting Governor Zhang 
Wule stressed: We are shouldering a very important task in our 
propaganda and ideological work. Through various effective 
propaganda means, we should arouse people's fighting will so 
that their spirit can be transformed into a powerful material 
force to accelerate the pace of pushing our province's economy 
to a new height. 
  In his speech, Zhang Wule first briefed participants on the 
present situation of economic operations in our province, and 
the good prospects of development. He fully affirmed the 
contributions made by the propaganda and ideological front to 
the economic and social development of the whole province. He 
pointed out: In the course of implementing the series of reform 
measures and policies promulgated by the state this year, 
correct propaganda and guidance in terms of public opinion are 
required. He said vividly: According to materialist dialectics, 
the spirit can be transformed into materials. Doing propaganda 
and ideological work well means creating wealth for economic 
development. He called on mass media and propaganda workers to 
understand the relationship between specific and general 
interests, partial and overall interests, and immediate and 
long-term interests; to conduct well the propaganda concerning 
hot and difficult topics; and to make still greater efforts to 
create a fine public-opinion environment for reform, opening up, 
and the economic construction of the whole province. 

</TEXT>

