<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gansu Sees Rapid Development of Township, Town Enterprises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2303052194 Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2303052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last year, the development of township and town 
enterprises in our province was at an all-time high, with their 
total production output value reaching approximately 17.7 
billion yuan, an increase of 58.37 percent over 1992. Total 
income in this sector was approximately 15.2 billion yuan, an 
increase of 53.36 percent. Peasants' per capita wage income 
from township and town enterprises has increased by 130 yuan, 
accounting for about one quarter of the peasants' per capita net 
income. 
  Last year, following the official promulgation of the State 
Council's decision on speeding up the development of township 
and town enterprises in the central and western regions, the 
whole province made the most of the resulting favorable 
situation to set off an upsurge of running township and town 
enterprises. Throughout the province, township and town 
enterprises in 14 counties, cities, and prefectures saw their 
development speed increase by more than 80 percent. In seven 
counties and prefectures, township and town enterprises doubled 
their pace of development. Township and town enterprises in 
Jiayuguan city increased their speed by 124 percent. On this 
basis, various localities made use of the new characteristic of 
the rapid development of township and town enterprises to 
transform them based on joint-stock and collective ownership to 
further define the relations between production and 
administrative power and tap investment potential. According to 
statistics, there are more than 3,700 large township and town 
enterprises under joint- stock collective ownership, and more 
than 1.2 billion yuan has been brought in. 
  In the course of developing township and town enterprises, 
various localities have generally attached importance to 
scientific and technical input. Last year, through various 
channels the whole province trained 24,000 qualified personnel 
with different expertise for township and town enterprises, 269 
of whom won middle ranking professional and technical titles for 
their posts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

