<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hong Kong Man's Lawsuit Against Qilihe Government Rejected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2803121294 Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2803121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The year-long lawsuit of Hong Kong businessman Tsui 
Bao-jen charging the Lanzhou Qilihe District People's Government 
with violating his rights as an agent was ruled on by the 
provincial higher people's court; and the case was closed with 
the accusant's charge rejected, and Tsui Bao-jen was to pay the 
cost of some 68,000 yuan involved in the trial. 
  A year before, Hong Kong businessman Tsui Bao-jen brought a 
case to the provincial higher people's court on the grounds that 
Qilihe District Government had violated his rights as an agent 
in marketing China-grown lily bulbs in Hong Kong because he had 
discovered an advertisement of the Hong Kong Maiya Trade Company 
claiming to be an agent in marketing lily bulbs, thus he 
demanded Qilihe District Government to acertain his general 
agent rights in Hong Kong, while claiming a 12.4 million yuan 
indemnity. 
  Through hearing of the provincial higher people's court, it 
was held that the contract signed between the accusant Tsui 
Bao-jen and the relavant department in Qilihe district 
explicitly stipulated that the term of Tsui Bao-jen acting as 
agent was five years. When the term expired, the contract was 
not renewed; consequently, Tsui's status of the agent ended 
automatically. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

