<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shaanxi Governor Makes Government Work Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1403072094 Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
0500 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1403072094 </F>
<F P=104>  Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Excerpts of Governor Bai Qingcai's government work report </F>
to the Second Session of the Eighth Provincial People's 
Congress," from the Special Coverage of the Second Session of 
the Eighth Provincial People's Congress -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] In his government work report to the second session 
of the eighth provincial people's congress, Bai Qingcai said: 
This year, we should continue to do a good job in planned 
parenthood and environmental protection, and should augment land 
administration. Planned parenthood, environmental protection, 
and land administration are three basic national policies of 
China. It is imperative to strengthen the sense of population 
and the per capita concept, to include population control in the 
overall plan for economic and social development, and to adhere 
to grasping two categories of production simultaneously. It is 
imperative to earnestly implement the Shaanxi provincial 
regulations on planned parenthood, with the focus on doing a 
good job in rural birth control. It is necessary to 
continuously complete and perfect the responsibility system with 
population target control, which must be under the charge of the 
chief responsible leading member, who will bear the chief 
responsibility. The system of veto without a ballot in birth 
control must be implemented resolutely so as to guarantee the 
fulfillment of the province's 1994 population plan. 
  Environmental protection has a direct bearing on economic 
and 
social development, and on people's physical well-being. It is 
imperative to adopt powerful measures to cure the worsening of 
the ecology; to adhere to the principle of harmonious 
development of environmental protection and economic 
construction; and to actively promote comprehensive urban and 
rural environmental improvement, with the focus on improving 
environmental pollution in Xian, Tongchuan, Yanan and the 
Northern Shaanxi Energy Resources Development Zone, so as to 
improve the environmental quality as quickly as possible. It is 
necessary to continue to augment environmental monitoring and 
control in order to avoid the surfacing of new sources of 
environmental pollution. It is necessary to improve the rate of 
handling industrial wastes, and to do a good job in protecting 
the sources of drinking water. 
  We should further magnify control over land resources and 
property management, and promote the rational allocation of land 
resources. Farmland should be protected in a down-to-earth way; 
the use of land for other than agricultural purposes must be 
strictly controlled. It is necessary to actively promote 
institutional reform in the use of state-owned land; the state 
is to monopolize the first-grade urban land market, but will 
lift control over and standardize the second-grade land market. 
The system of assessing and making public basic land prices is 
to be established. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

