<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diversified Economy Helps Shaanxi Peasants </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2403081894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0749 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2403081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Xian, March 24 (XINHUA) -- Peasants in northwest 
China's Shaanxi Province have benefited from developing a 
diversified economy. 
  Last year, the growing of economic crops, vegetables and 
fruit, and animal husbandry helped local farmers increase per 
capita income by 347 yuan, a 53 percent rise. 
  The provincial government has announced preferential 
policies 
and provided funds for farmers to develop a diversified economy. 
  More than 40 diversified economy projects in rural areas 
have 
been designated as key ones to receive favorable policies in 
funds and materials. 
  The planting area of apple trees was increased from 193,000 
ha in 1990 to 339,000 ha. Last year, with an annual output of 
300,000 tons to 1.31 million tons. 
  Vegetable areas were increased by 66,600 ha. 
  In 1993 some 15 of the key projects produced a total income 
of nearly six billion yuan (about 700 million U.S. dollars) for 
the local peasants. 
  Commodity production bases of chicken, pork, vegetables, 
pears, edible oil, apples, tobacco, mushrooms and dates have 
emerged in various localities. 
  At the same time, the province attaches importance to 
developing cold-storage, processing, packaging and 
transportation facilities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

