<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam Ends Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003083394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0753 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003083394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Kim Yong-sam, 
president of the Republic of Korea (ROK), and his party left 
here for home at noon today at the end of their five-day 
official visit to China. 
  They were seen off at the airport by Wu Jichuan, chairman of 
the Chinese Government Reception Committee and minister of posts 
and telecommunications, and Zhang Lichang, mayor of Tianjin city. 
  After their arrival from Beijing this morning, Kim and his 
party officials heard a briefing by Zhang on Tianjin's economic 
growth and the construction of a development zone in the city. 
  Kim also inspected a ROK industrial park and the ROK-funded 
Sae-Han Precision Corporation Ltd. 
  He described the park as "very useful" to ROK-Tianjin 
cooperation and to ROK-China cooperation at large. 
  Kim told the hosts that following his visit, more ROK 
businessmen will invest in Tianjin. 

