<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK Investment Increases in Tianjin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2703141194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1347 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2703141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, March 27 (XINHUA) -- Investment from the 
Republic of Korea (ROK) in north China's port city of Tianjin 
has kept going up in recent years. 
  Some 275 enterprises with ROK's investment have been set up 
in the city since 1992. The ROK investors have put in 260 
million U.S. dollars in these enterprises. 
  The firms are mainly engaged in industry, agriculture, 
construction, real estate, transport and services. The greatest 
number -- some 212 of them -- are in industrial production and 
have made good profits. 
  The Tianjin Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd., a joint venture to 
produce video-corders, funded by Tianjin Telecommunication and 
Broadcasting Company and Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd of the ROK, 
went into production in October last year. Its video-corders 
are the first from China to enter the international market, and 
the company plans to export 120,000 video-corders this year. 
  In the Tianjin economic and technological development zone, 
an 1,156,000 sq m site has been leased to ROK investors for 50 
years. Land leveling is expected to be finished next year. 

</TEXT>

