<F P=102>  OW2603010194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1446 
GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2603010194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, 22 Mar (XINHUA) -- While talking about his 
impressions of his trip to China, Japanese Prime Minister 
Morihiro Hosokawa said today at a social gathering attended by 
his cabinet members after a cabinet meeting that his meetings 
with Chinese leaders are of great significance. 
  Hosokawa said that, during his visit to China, he not only 
discussed with Chinese leaders the issues of bilateral relations 
between Japan and China, but also conducted significant meetings 
with them on a wide variety of subjects such as U.S.-China 
relations and human rights. 
  He stressed that, through this trip, he has made China 
understand that the current Japanese Government attaches 
importance to China. 
  Hosokawa pointed out that China has achieved remarkable 
development, and its market is very important to Japan's 
economy. Meanwhile, he held that Japan is relatively slow in 
entering this great market in China. 

</TEXT>

