<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sino-British Financial Seminar Held in Beijing 15 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503105194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1020 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 15 (XINHUA) -- A financial seminar, 
aimed at boosting the financial cooperation between China and 
Britain, was held here today. 
  With "Developing a capital market in London -- China's 
international gateway" as its theme, another session of the 
seminar will open in Shanghai on March 17. 
  Sir Andrew Smith, visiting chairman of the London Stock 
Exchange, gave a keynote address on what the London Stock 
Exchange is to economic development in China. 
  Jing Shuping, chairman of the China International Economic 
Consultants Inc. and chairman of the Stock Exchange Executive 
Council, gave an opening address. 
  Jointly held by the China-Britain Trade Group and British 
Invisibles, the seminar aims to acquaint Chinese financial 
personnel with the British experience in raising international 
finances and promote Sino-British cooperation in this and other 
areas. 
  Some dozen British bankers, lawyers and financial experts 
delivered lectures to the Chinese audience on British experience 
in developing its domestic capital market, the requirements for 
the listing of companies on overseas markets and project 
financing. 
  About 200 Chinese from relevant government departments, 
banks 
and enterprises attended the seminar. 

</TEXT>

