<H3> <TI>   NPC Chairman Qiao Shi Meets Danish Parliamentarians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803123394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1152 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 28 (XINHUA) -- Chairman Qiao Shi of 
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) 
had a 40- minutes discussion with a group of Danish 
parliamentarians on the furtherance of Sino-Danish ties. 
  Briefing the visitors on China's foreign policy, Qiao told 
the visitors that China supports all endeavors conducive to the 
maintenance of world peace and is ready to expand contacts with 
as many countries as possible. 
  Qiao described Sino-Danish ties as "good" and reiterated 
that 
China wants to have still better relations with Denmark on the 
principles of seeking common ground while reserving differences, 
mutual respect, non-interference in each other's internal 
affairs, equality and mutual benefit. 
  Qiao also briefed the visitors on the reform and opening up 
in China, particularly the development in Tibet Autonomous 
Region. 
  Peter Duetoft, leader of the visiting group and chairman of 
the foreign policies committee of the Danish parliament, told 
Qiao that the purpose of their visit is to learn about China's 
economic development, which is of significance to Denmark. 
  Denmark wants to see more exchanges between the two 
parliaments and stronger economic ties between the two countries 
because China is a vast market, he said. 
  Earlier today, Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister 
Qian 
Qichen met the visitors and explained China's position on some 
international issues including China's view on the role of the 
United Nations. 
  Qian and the Danish parliamentarians agreed that the two 
sides will make joint efforts for the development of Sino-Danish 
political and economic ties, according to a Chinese official. 

</TEXT>

