<F P=102>  OW2703140994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1351 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2703140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 27 (XINHUA) -- Air China today opened 
a new international air route from Shanghai, China's biggest 
industrial city, to Frankfurt, Germany. 
  The non-stop 13-hour flight by Boeing 747-400 is scheduled 
to 
fly every Sunday, Tuesday and Thursday. 
  In Beijing, the China Xinhua Airlines (CXA) today announced 
new scheduled flights to provincial capital cities including 
Xian, Haikou, Jinan and Kunmin, expanding Xinhua's total of air 
routes to 14. 
  Founded in August, 1992, the CXA now has four Boeing 737-300 
planes, running nine of the domestic air routes from Tianjin to 
Shenzhen, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Harbin. 

