<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group Meeting Ends in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2603043994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0403 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2603043994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 26 (XINHUA) -- The 19th meeting of 
the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group ended here yesterday 
with the two sides signing a summary of talks on aviation 
agreements between the Macao Government and Belgium, Luxemburg 
and the Netherlands. 
  The two sides stressed the importance of the three 
agreements 
on the projected Macao international airport, according to a 
press communique issued at the end of the three-day meeting. 
  The Portuguese side also provided the Chinese side with a 
copy of an aviation agreement initialed with Brazil. 
  The communique says that the two sides had long discussions 
on localization of public servants, the official status of the 
Chinese Language as well as the translation and localization of 
laws. They also reviewed the progress made on these issues. 
  On international organizations, the two sides have taken 
note 
of the fact that the two governments have formally applied in 
Geneva for Macao's membership in the World Meteorological 
Organization. 
  Taking note of the fact that the International Navigation 
Association has of late revised its constitution, the two sides 
reiterated their concern on macao going through the process in 
joining the association. 
  The two sides also studied progress made by the work group 
on 
the Bank of China and the Atlantic Bank participating in issuing 
bank notes. They asked the group to continue with its work. 
  The two sides, in an atmosphere of friendship and 
cooperation, discussed important issues related to Macao's 
social development and stability, including nationality of some 
Macao residents, says the communique. 
  It was agreed that the 20th meeting of the Sino-Portuguese 
Joint Liaison Group is to be held in Lisbon beginning from July 
5. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

