<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaison Group Issues Communique </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2703004394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0507 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2703004394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 26 Mar (XINHUA) -- The 19th session of the 
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group has released a press 
communique. The full text reads: 
  The 19th session of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group 
took place in Beijing 22-25 March. 
  The two sides had a long discussion on issues concerning the 
localization of civil servants, the official status of the 
Chinese Language, and translation and localization of laws; and 
studied the progress in dealing with these issues. 
  The two sides signed the minutes of talks concerning the 
aviation agreements which the Macao Government had reached with 
the Governments of Belgium, Luxembourg, and the Netherlands; and 
they underscored the significance of these agreements for the 
future Macao international airport. The Portuguese side 
furnished the Chinese side for study the text of the aviation 
agreement which Portugal had initialled with Brazil. 
  With regard to international organizations, the two sides 
took note of the requests about Macao's access to the World 
Organization of Meteorology, which the governments of the two 
countries had officially submitted in Geneva. The two sides 
also took note that the International Association of Navigation 
Marks had revised its charter, and the two sides reaffirmed 
their attention to the process Macao will go through in joining 
the organization. 
  The two sides also studied the progress made by the working 
panel of the Bank of China and the Atlantic Bank on their 
participation in issuing currency, and instructed the panel to 
proceed with its work. 
  The two sides also discussed major issues relevant to 
Macao's 
economic development and social stability, as well as the issue 
concerning the nationality of some residents in Macao. 
  The meeting proceeded in an amicable and cooperative 
atmosphere. 
  The 20th session of the PRC-Portuguese Liaison Group will 
take place in Lisbon beginning 5 July. 

</TEXT>

