<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Attends Meeting of Liaoning Delegation to NPC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1403121594 Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1403121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 13 March at Liaoning hall of the Great Hall of 
the People, the delegation of Liaoning Province participating in 
the second session of the eighth National People's Congress 
[NPC] held a plenary meeting to discuss Premier Li Peng's 
government work report in line with the reality of Liaoning. 
  Present at the meeting were Zou Jiahua, vice premier of the 
State Council; Chen Muhua, vice premier of the State Council, 
vice chairman of the NPC standing committee, and chairman of the 
national women's federation; Liu Qi, minister at the Ministry of 
Metallurgical Industry; and leaders of the state departments 
concerned. Quan Shuren, chairman of the provincial people's 
congress standing committee, chaired the meeting. Gu Jinchi, 
secretary of the provincial party committee, made a speech ahead 
of others. 
  He said: Premier Li Peng's report is of essential, 
comprehensive, and profound importance and embodies the ideas of 
seeking truth, dealing with concrete matters relating to work, 
doing pioneering work, and making progress. I completely agree 
to it. As for Liaoning, an urgent task for understanding the 
basic guidelines of the report and fulfilling the tasks as set 
forth in the report is to start from the change of the 
managerial mechanism to speed up the enlivening of state-owned 
large and medium-sized enterprises. This is the key to 
deepening reform, promoting development, and realizing the 
second pioneering work. 
  After that, Governor Yue Qifeng made a speech. He talked 
about the understanding about the report; introduced, in detail, 
to Vice Premier Zou Jiahua and NPC Vice Chairman Chen Muhua the 
province's achievements in reform and opening up made in 1993; 
and reported on the province's problems and difficulties in 
accelerating the setup of the market economy. 
  Deputies (Li Huazhong) and (Bo Xilai) set forth their 
suggestions and viewpoints on how to accelerate the development 
of large and medium-sized enterprises and to promote 
agricultural production and the opening of the province to the 
outside world. 
  Zou Jiahua, vice premier of the State Council, finally made 
a 
speech. 
  He said: Today, we mainly want to hear your opinions on the 
report and what methods you have to solve the existing problems, 
to draw on collective wisdom and absorb all useful ideas, to 
make preparations for the next-step arrangements, and to ensure 
a sound and orderly development of the economy. 
  He said: Last year, Liaoning made better economic 
development and made a big headway in agriculture. Being 
self-sufficient in grain and nonstaple foods was a great 
achievement. Agriculture is the foundation of the national 
economy. Therefore, strengthening the agricultural development 
is of great strategic significance and must be persisted in. 
  He expressed his views on accelerating the transformation of 
large and medium-sized enterprises. He said: I completely 
agreed to your suggestions on conducting technological 
transformation. Liaoning's state-owned large and medium-sized 
enterprises have a good foundation. So, these enterprises 
should fully be transformed and utilized so as to become 
vigorous. 
  He also stressed: The products produced after technological 
transformation must be marketable. Without marketing channels, 
the products, no matter how good they are, will be of no use. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

