<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Take Stronger Measures Against Fake Commodities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2903171994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1555 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (XINHUA) -- A national meeting 
was held here today to further crack down this year on fake 
goods and imitations. 
  Xu Penghang, vice minister in charge of the State Economic 
and Trade Commission, presided over the meeting and urged the 
administrative bodies to pay major attention to cracking down on 
phony medicines, foodstuff, export goods, agricultural 
production materials and building materials and trade marks, and 
to deal with ten major cases already under investigation. 
  He pointed out that a safeguarding system should be 
established, adding that more cases of fake goods had been 
exposed with the joint efforts of procuratorates and local 
governments. 
  Last year the procuratorates of China dealt with 3,436 
cases, 
recovering a sum of 72.34 million yuan. 

</TEXT>

