<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Receives Approval for Foreign Currency Exchange </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003073994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0719 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, March 30 (XINHUA) -- East China's 
Zhejiang Province is to have its first exchange market for 
foreign currency in April. 
  Approved by the Zhejiang branch of the State Administration 
of Exchange Control, the market will be run by the international 
trust and investment company of the province. 
  Investors, including state-owned enterprises, Sino-foreign 
joint ventures, private businesses and individuals, can trade on 
the market in the prime hard currencies, such as U.S. dollars, 
Deutsche marks, Japanese yen, pounds sterling and Swiss francs. 
  The market will be able to display the latest world market 
exchange rates, as it will be linked up with the terminals of 
REUTERS NEWS AGENCY. 

</TEXT>

